Subject: [PATCH 6/6] ggml-cuda: TurboQuant TQ3_0 / TQ4_0 flash-attention support

Target: PrismML-Eng/llama.cpp tag prism-b9596-9fcaed7, after patches 0001-0005.

- fattn-common.cuh: dequantize_V_tq3_0/tq4_0 (per-thread closed-form parity-sum
  inverse RHT; the vec kernel calls with ne == 4 and i0 % 4 == 0, so a group
  never straddles a 32-block) + get_dequantize_V dispatch entries.
- fattn.cu: support-check gating — the mixed pair K = F16/Q8_0 with
  V = TQ3_0/TQ4_0 is explicitly allowed in ALL builds (bypasses the
  no-GGML_CUDA_FA_ALL_QUANTS K != V restriction); any other K paired with a
  TurboQuant V returns BEST_FATTN_KERNEL_NONE so it can never reach the vec
  dispatch abort (the op then falls back to another backend, never crashes).
  Vec dispatch cases for the four supported pairs are always compiled.
- fattn-vec.cuh: extern template declarations for the new instances.
- template-instances: 4 new fattn-vec instance files (K in {f16, q8_0} x V in
  {tq3_0, tq4_0}, head dims 64/128/256 — Bonsai uses 128 and 256), and
  generate_cu_files.py regenerates them.
- CMakeLists.txt: the TQ instances are compiled in BOTH build flavors (with
  and without GGML_CUDA_FA_ALL_QUANTS). suiban's `apply_patches.py --cuda`
  still passes -DGGML_CUDA_FA_ALL_QUANTS=ON so every non-suiban mixed K/V
  pair also works; the flag is not required for the suiban pairs.

Decoding V=TQ4_0 rows in the vec kernel costs ~32 adds per output element
(the inverse rotation mixes the whole block) — a reference implementation,
correctness first. TODO(v1.1): warp-cooperative shfl-butterfly fast path if
the decode-bound long-context case shows up in profiling.
